AdvisorModule.Caption: Object in experiment does not run
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when an object is created from the Toolbox in E-Studio or as part of an InLine with E-Basic but never has its .Run call occur in the experiment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Volatile Clock on Windows XP
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the E-Prime Primary Clock is configured in a way that could cause timing inconsistencies. Contact PST Tech Support to configure the clock for more stabilized configuration when using Windows XP with this finding.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Procedure ends with pending InputMask objects
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when there are input masks that continue to collect responses at the end of a Procedure. Use of the TimeLimit option of (until feedback), (end of proc), and Procedure.ProcessLastObjectPendingInputMasks can ensure that responses are not collected and not properly logged.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Movie and audio stimuli not mapped
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when when a movie or audio file is not using mappings available through CodecConfig. Using auto connect can increase load times and does not provide the consistency for replicating paradigms on the experiment computer.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Duration not divisible by refresh rate
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when an an object with an OnsetSync=(vertical blank) has a Duration value that is not divisible by the DisplayDevice calulated refresh rate which can lead to larger OnsetDelay and other timing issues.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Non-Visual object using OnsetSync or OffsetSync
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a non visual object (SoundOut, SoundIn, Wait) has either of its OnsetSync or OffsetSync properties set to (vertical blank) which is usually unecessary unless sync with external equipment

AdvisorModule.Caption: Text object has matching BackColor and ForeColor
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a TextDisplay or SlideText object has an opaque BackStyle with an identical value for BackColor and ForeColor which can lead to an object not being visible during an experiment.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Use of ClearAfter
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a visual object uses ClearAfter. ClearAfter can cause display timing anomalies and does not provide the robust logging that the Onset of an object can provide. ClearAfter and should be considered deprecated and will be removed in a future version of E-Prime. Instead of using ClearAfter, consider using an empty TextDisplay object immediately following that has a Height and Width property that will cover the screen.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Large OnsetDelay
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when an object has on OnsetDelay that is larger than a single refresh. Using a Duration that is divisible by the refresh rate and a value of PreRelease=(same as duration) will typically reduce OnsetDelay values

AdvisorModule.Caption: Use of WaitForVerticalBlank when FlippingEnabled
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when the DisplayDevice.WaitForVerticalBlank E-Basic command is used when the DisplayDevice.FlippingEnabled property is Yes/True. Calling WaitForVerticalBlank while flipping can cause timing concerns.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Direct Canvas Commands
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a Canvas command other than Copy is invoked that would directly alter the screen contents. It is recommended to perform all Canvas drawing on an offscreen Canvas and then use the Copy method to display the contents to the screen.

AdvisorModule.Caption: Evaluate SoundDevice.API
AdvisorModule.Description: Detects when a SoundDevice is using the DirectSound(TM) API on Windows Vista or later which typically cannot achieve latency values under 30ms. ASIO or CoreAudio recommended for Windows Vista or later. Use SoundTester to choose the most appropriate API for the experiment computer.
